custom-block.l: You can create a new file by selecting the "New Game" option on the main menu and selecting a file. Selecting a file that already exists will overwrite that file.
To load a file, select the "Continue" option on the main menu, and then select the file.
You can delete a file by selecting the "Delete File" option on the main menu and selecting a file. You will then be asked for confirmation.

When a file is shown in the main menu, several pieces of metadata are shown. In order, these are the file number, the name of the character in that file, the level of the character, the time the files was created, and the last time the file was modified.
Files are stored in the local storage of your browser, with 5 entries per file, for a total of 15 entries.

You can change a setting by selecting the "Settings" option on the main menu, selecting the setting you want to change, and, depending on the type of setting, selecting either the new value of the setting, or the "Change..." option.
You can reset a setting by using the same method as changing the setting, but selecting the "Reset to Default" option.
Settings are stored in the local storage of your browser, with a single entry containing the values of all settings.
Health works like it does in most games; it has a maximum, and if it hits zero, you die. Your maximum health is increased when you level up.
Exp is gained over time, from doing things like killing mobs or leveling up skills. Once you gain enough exp, you'll level up, increasing some of your stats.
Your attack increases the amount of damage you deal to enemies. It can be increased by equipping weapons, or by leveling up.
Your defense decreases the amount of damage you take from enemies. It can be increased by equipping armor, or by leveling up.
When you roll for attack or defense, you roll a 1dX, where X is your indirect stat, which then has your direct stat added to it.
Your kills stat tracks the number of times you've killed an enemy.
Your deaths stat tracks the number of times you've died.

When you use a skill, you'll gain experience in that skill, proportional to the roll you got and your current level in that skill. Once you gain enough skill exp, you'll level up in that skill, increasing your efficiency in that skill.
Chopping is the primary method of obtaining items like logs or sticks. To go chopping, find a tree and interact with it. Boosted by: Axe
Mining is the primary method of obtaining items like cobblestone or ores. To go mining, find an ore node and interact with it. Boosted by: Pickaxe
Digging is the primary method of obtaining items like dirt or gravel. To go digging, find a pile of diggable material, like dirt or sand, and interact with it. Boosted by: Shovel
Fishing is the primary method of obtaining fish, plus a few other items. To go fishing, find a puddle and interact with it. Boosted by: Fishing Rod

Gathering is the primary method of obtaining items that can't be obtained through other methods. To go gathering, find a gather node, like a glowing spot or a pile of leaves, and interact with it. Boosted by: None
Crafting is the primary method of making items out of other items. To craft something, press the [R] key, and find the item in the recipe list. Boosted by: Hammer
Cooking is the primary method of making food. To cook something, press the [R] key, switch to the Cooking menu, and find the item in the recipe list. Boosted by: Spatula
